						<summary>

						<p>On the right side of the south <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Viṭṭhalasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Achyuta, 1539 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record, in Sankrit verse, is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1461,</hi> expressed by the chronogram <hi rend="bold">Chandra-rasa-amara-indra, Vikāri, Bhādrapada śu. 12, Tuesday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1539 A.D., August 26, °36.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers the gift of <hi rend="bold">Ānandanidhi</hi> to the Brāhmaṇas by the king.</p>						

